menu "breadboard: bb_fan"

config BB_FAN_AUTOFAN
    bool "Enable autofan PID controller in bb_fan"
    default n
    help
        When enabled, bb_fan owns a PID-based autofan controller that runs
        inside bb_fan_poll(). Parameters are a faithful port of TaipanMiner's
        proven autofan: Kp=5 Ki=0.1 Kd=2, P_ON_E, REVERSE direction,
        5000 ms sample time, dual EMA (alpha=0.2) for die and aux (VR) temps,
        input-src selected by max((ema-target)/target) ratio.

        When enabled, PATCH /api/sensors (bb_sensor_http, fan section) parses
        autofan config fields (autofan, die_target_c, vr_target_c, manual_pct,
        min_pct) instead of raw duty_pct. GET /api/sensors gains additional
        telemetry fields (die_ema_c, vr_ema_c, pid_input_c, pid_input_src).

        Consumers that feed aux (VR) temperature must call bb_fan_set_aux_temp()
        periodically. bb_fan does not depend on bb_power; the consumer is
        responsible for reading the VR sensor and feeding it here.

        Default off — enable when your app wants bb_fan to own autofan policy.

endmenu
